{
  "stem": "18102.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 124.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This was a critical decision, of course, because it was so [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] momentous to, to, to consider that all of the ones that returned with the safety of the Russian Army thought they would certainly be OK and were arrested by the NKVD and never heard from again.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Clearly, that would have been our fate.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because when they were sent to Siberia, it wasn't just them-- not the menfolk.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was the whole family.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so we, too, would have ended up somewhere in Siberia.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, I'm sure.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'm sure all of this played itself out the rest of my life, in terms of fear and, and what I began to, to, to understand, my mother's so-called Bialystok Syndrome, that danger lurks around every corner.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I, I guess I lived my life having that feeling transmitted by virtue of these events and my mother's feeling.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I guess it served me in many ways, because I always thought ahead as a consequence.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And, you know, when I'm accredited in, in the marketplace with having vision, I think that vision was based on this fear factor.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You've gotta think ahead to survive, which is true in business as well as in ordinary life.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I think that certainly was the beginning of it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You have to.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, it's the what-if scenarios.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Obviously, it's the, it's the similar thing that the Pentagon does in its war room, you know, eventualities and what-if situations and the worst kind, the best kind, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You prepare.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And in my mind, that was always going on as an adult.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I think it clearly has its origin in these events of the early days of my life and in Bialystok.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
